        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What are the best small cap value stocks for 2026?</h3>
                <p>The best small cap value stocks for 2026 combine strong fundamentals with discounted valuations. Our strict screen requires a market cap between $300M and $2B, a Price-to-Earnings (P/E) ratio under 15, Price-to-Book (P/B) under 1.5, and positive recent earnings.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How do you find undervalued small cap stocks?</h3>
                <p>Finding undervalued small cap stocks involves screening for low valuation multiples (P/E, P/B, P/S) relative to historical averages and peers, combined with positive cash flow, manageable debt, and catalysts like insider buying.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Why invest in small cap value stocks in 2026?</h3>
                <p>Small cap value stocks often present significant upside potential because they are less followed by institutional analysts. In environments with favorable interest rates, deeply discounted smaller companies can see multiple expansion.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What is considered a small cap stock?</h3>
                <p>A small cap stock typically represents a company with a total market capitalization between $300 million and $2 billion. They sit between micro-caps and mid-caps in terms of size and risk.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is insider buying a good sign for undervalued small caps?</h3>
                <p>Yes, insider buying is historically a strong bullish signal, especially in small cap value stocks. It indicates that executives who know the company best believe the current stock price severely underestimates the company's true intrinsic value.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    
  
